      "message": "I have been testing on Chromebooks (ARM Cortex A15, A17, A72 and A53). Initially, I extracted the blit_row_s32a_opaque function and compiled it independently (outside Skia) with different compilers (gcc 6.2.1 and clang 4.0) for various ARM Chromebooks. Later, I integrated the NEON version in Skia and compiled it again for ARM Chromebooks. I ran the unit tests (dm) and nanobench benchmarks (repeating 3 times with and without patch with --samples 100) to ensure I could provide numbers that were meaningful to you.",
