      "writtenOn": "2017-05-15T13:20:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think any of SkPMSrcOver, SkMulDiv255Round, or the previous code are\nreally correct.  It looks like we had a \"TODO: this math is wrong\" in the old\ncode.  Why don\u0027t we take this opportunity to fix it?  Doing the right thing\nhere will give this code greater longevity; as it is, I\u0027m more inclined to\ndelete these optimizations than maintain inconsistent math.\n\nLet\u0027s see if we can get the same results in fixed point that we\u0027d have gotten\nin floats (just an arbitrary format with more than enough precision).\n\nWe\u0027re trying to implement this abstract function, right?\n\n   srcover(src,src_alpha,dst) \u003d src + (1 - src_alpha) * dst\n\nPromoting 8-bit to floats, our reference function is\n\n    uint8_t srcover_float(uint8_t src, uint8_t src_alpha, uint8_t dst) {\n        float S \u003d src       * (1/255.0f),\n              A \u003d src_alpha * (1/255.0f),\n              D \u003d dst       * (1/255.0f);\n\n        float R \u003d S + (1 - A) * D;\n        return R * 255.0f + 0.5f;\n    }\n\nA naive fixed point version that produces all the same outputs is\n\n    uint8_t srcover_div(uint8_t src, uint8_t src_alpha, uint8_t dst) {\n        return src + ((255 - src_alpha) * dst + 127) / 255;\n    }\n\n/255 makes that undesirable.  Here\u0027s a version that only uses \u003e\u003e8\n\n    uint8_t srcover_shift8(uint8_t src, uint8_t src_alpha, uint8_t dst) {\n        uint16_t p \u003d (255 - src_alpha) * dst;\n        return src + ((p + ((p+128)\u003e\u003e8) + 128)\u003e\u003e8);\n    }\n\nI wrote that a little weirdly so that some parts like the +128s and \u003e\u003e8s stand out.\nThis should make the transition to the next version of the function more clear.\nIf we use the fun toys you guys provide in NEON, a lot of this folds together.\n\n    uint8_t srcover_neon1(uint8_t src, uint8_t src_alpha, uint8_t dst) {\n        uint8x8_t S \u003d vdup_n_u8(src),\n                  A \u003d vdup_n_u8(src_alpha),\n                  D \u003d vdup_n_u8(dst);\n\n        uint16x8_t P \u003d vmull_u8(vdup_n_u8(255) - A, D);\n        uint8x8_t R \u003d S + vraddhn_u16(P, vrshrq_n_u16(P, 8));\n        return R[0];\n    }\n\nWhile we\u0027re at it, people usually write srcover as src + (1 - src_alpha) * dst,\nbut it\u0027s just as good to write src + dst - src_alpha*dst.  I like this best.\n\n    uint8_t srcover_neon2(uint8_t src, uint8_t src_alpha, uint8_t dst) {\n        uint8x8_t S \u003d vdup_n_u8(src),\n                  A \u003d vdup_n_u8(src_alpha),\n                  D \u003d vdup_n_u8(dst);\n\n        uint16x8_t P \u003d vmull_u8(A, D);\n        uint8x8_t R \u003d S + D - vraddhn_u16(P, vrshrq_n_u16(P, 8));\n        return R[0];\n    }\n\nHere\u0027s the driver I used to test all this:\n\n    #define srcover_fixed srcover_...\n    int main(void) {\n        for (int       dst \u003d 0;       dst \u003c\u003d 255;       dst++)\n        for (int src_alpha \u003d 0; src_alpha \u003c\u003d 255; src_alpha++)\n        for (int       src \u003d 0; src_alpha \u003e\u003d src;       src++) {\n\n            if (srcover_float(src, src_alpha, dst) !\u003d srcover_fixed(src, src_alpha, dst)) {\n                printf(\"%02x/%02x over %02x\\n\", src, src_alpha, dst);\n                return 1;\n            }\n        }\n\n        printf(\"ok\\n\");\n        return 0;\n    }",
      "revId": "cb2f18af0ac87c34e010a0d3b695ed5911735893",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
