        "id": 6920
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-17T18:35:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Well, the runs I carried out revealed that this branch in the middle of the loop is not cheap for sure. Concerning the readback from NEON I think you are referring to\n\n  http://infocenter.arm.com/help/index.jsp?topic\u003d/com.arm.doc.ddi0344k/ch16s05s02.html\n\nThis doesn\u0027t affect newer cores, but the readback has a non-negligible performance hit if compared to moving between registers of the same type. For newer cores you can look into the Software Optimisation Guides. For ARM Cortex A72 this would be:\n\n  http://infocenter.arm.com/help/topic/com.arm.doc.uan0016a/cortex_a72_software_optimization_guide_external.pdf\n\n\"VMOV\" is at section 3.11 \"FP Miscellaneous Instructions\", page 18.",
